     fhir:Narrative.div "<div xml:lang=\"en\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" lang=\"en\"><p class=\"res-header-id\"><b>Narratif généré : CodeSystem v3-TimingEvent</b></p><a name=\"v3-TimingEvent\"> </a><a name=\"hcv3-TimingEvent\"> </a><div style=\"display: inline-block; background-color: #d9e0e7; padding: 6px; margin: 4px; border: 1px solid #8da1b4; border-radius: 5px; line-height: 60%\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px\">version : 1; Dernière mise à jour : 2026-01-07 10:12:52+0100; Langue : en</p></div><p><b>Propriétés</b></p><p><b>Cette terminologie de référence (CodeSystem) définit les propriétés suivantes pour ses concepts</b></p><table class=\"grid\"><tr><td><b>Nom</b></td><td><b>Code</b></td><td><b>URI</b></td><td><b>Type</b></td><td><b>Description</b></td></tr><tr><td>internalId</td><td>internalId</td><td>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/utg-concept-properties#v3-internal-id</td><td>code</td><td>The internal identifier for the concept in the HL7 Access database repository.</td></tr><tr><td>status</td><td>status</td><td>http://hl7.org/fhir/concept-properties#status</td><td>code</td><td>Designation of a concept's state. Normally is not populated unless the state is retired.</td></tr><tr><td>HL7 Concept Usage Notes</td><td>HL7usageNotes</td><td>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/utg-concept-properties#HL7usageNotes</td><td>string</td><td>HL7 Concept Usage Notes</td></tr></table><p><b>Concepts</b></p><p>This case-sensitive code system <code>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-TimingEvent</code> defines the following codes dans une hiérarchie Is-A:</p><table class=\"codes\"><tr><td><b>Niv</b></td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Définition</b></td><td><b>internalId</b></td><td><b>status</b></td><td><b>HL7 Concept Usage Notes</b></td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">AC<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-AC\"> </a></td><td><div><p>before meal (from lat. ante cibus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10708</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ACD<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-ACD\"> </a></td><td><div><p>before lunch (from lat. ante cibus diurnus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10712</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ACM<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-ACM\"> </a></td><td><div><p>before breakfast (from lat. ante cibus matutinus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10711</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ACV<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-ACV\"> </a></td><td><div><p>before dinner (from lat. ante cibus vespertinus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10713</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">C<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-C\"> </a></td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> meal (from lat. ante cibus)</p>\n</div></td><td>22717</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  CD<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-CD\"> </a></td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> lunch (from lat. cibus diurnus)</p>\n</div></td><td>22719</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  CM<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-CM\"> </a></td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> breakfast (from lat. cibus matutinus)</p>\n</div></td><td>22718</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  CV<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-CV\"> </a></td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> dinner (from lat. cibus vespertinus)</p>\n</div></td><td>22720</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">HS<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-HS\"> </a></td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> Prior to beginning a regular period of extended sleep (this would exclude naps). Note that this might occur at different times of day depending on a person's regular sleep schedule.</p>\n</div></td><td>10707</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">IC<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-IC\"> </a></td><td><div><p>between meals (from lat. inter cibus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10710</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ICD<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-ICD\"> </a></td><td><div><p>between lunch and dinner</p>\n</div></td><td>10718</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ICM<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-ICM\"> </a></td><td><div><p>between breakfast and lunch</p>\n</div></td><td>10717</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">ICV<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-ICV\"> </a></td><td><div><p>between dinner and the hour of sleep</p>\n</div></td><td>10719</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">PC<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-PC\"> </a></td><td><div><p>after meal (from lat. post cibus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10709</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">PCD<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-PCD\"> </a></td><td><div><p>after lunch (from lat. post cibus diurnus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10715</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">PCM<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-PCM\"> </a></td><td><div><p>after breakfast (from lat. post cibus matutinus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10714</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">PCV<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-PCV\"> </a></td><td><div><p>after dinner (from lat. post cibus vespertinus)</p>\n</div></td><td>10716</td><td>active</td><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">WAKE<a name=\"v3-TimingEvent-WAKE\"> </a></td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> Upon waking up from a regular period of sleep, in order to start regular activities (this would exclude waking up from a nap or temporarily waking up during a period of sleep)</p>\n<p><strong>Usage Notes:</strong> e.g.</p>\n<p>Take pulse rate on waking in management of thyrotoxicosis.</p>\n<p>Take BP on waking in management of hypertension</p>\n<p>Take basal body temperature on waking in establishing date of ovulation</p>\n</div></td><td>22721</td><td>active</td><td>e.g. Take pulse rate on waking in management of thyrotoxicosis. Take BP on waking in management of hypertension Take basal body temperature on waking in establishing date of ovulation</td></tr></table></div>"
  ] ;
